enhanced_by.reason: The start() method initializes the collating state, which is necessary before invoking hasNext().
Adding iterators is a prerequisite for the hasNext() method to function correctly.
The anyHasNext(List) method is directly invoked within hasNext() to check if any child iterator has remaining elements.
The anyValueSet(BitSet) method is directly invoked within hasNext() to check if any value has been set in the valueSet.
